Title/Headline (if applicable): Best Foot Beacon: Henry David Thoreau
Body / Key Message (if applicable): Go confidently in the direction of your dreams. Live the life you’ve imagined.
The only sure way to avoid making mistakes is to have no new ideas.
Worrying is like paying a debt you don't owe.
Know that you can start late, look different, be uncertain and still succeed.
Keep your face always toward the sunshine - and shadows will fall behind you.
Interest is the most important thing in life: happiness is temporary, but interest is continuous.
Worrying does not empty tomorrow of its troubles: it empties today of its strength.
Spread More Love Today
Some people find fault like there’s a reward for it.
It’s not who you are that holds you back into you think you are not.
Friendship Needs No Reason.
Always Leave People Better Than You Found Them.
You have the power to say “This is not how the story ends.”
Love yourself as if you are a rainbow with gold at both ends.
Get in the way. Make good trouble.
Life is short. Take the trip. Buy the shoes. Eat the cake.
If you change nothing - nothing will change.
Failure is not the opposite of success: it’s part of success.
Look for the helpers.
Keep calm: they hate that.
Time spent amongst trees is never wasted time.
Today - Seek Wisdom
You had the power all along, my dear.
No one is more worthy of your kindness and compassion than you are.
The smallest act of kindness is worth more than the greatest intention.
For lovely eyes, seek out the good in people.
